{When tourism developed at the Spanish coast, it became feasible to organize a
chess event during the off-season. A long series of master tournaments was
played at the Costa del Sol in Torremolinos or Malaga. The first event
happened at Hotel Pez Espada from 24 i until 7 ii 1961. Six Spaniards and six
foreigners competed. It became a race between Gligoric and Pomar Salamanca.
Portisch and Najdorf were other main participants. We follow all decided games
by Gligoric and Pomar plus four extra games.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4.
e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nbd7 8. Re1 c6 9. Bf1 a5 10. Rb1 Re8 11. b3
Ng4 12. d5 $1 {The pawn moves forwards at a fine moment.} c5 $2 ({Better is} 
12... Nc5) 13. h3 Nh6 14. Nb5 Nf8 15. a3 f5 16. Nd2 Nf7 17. b4 b6 18. bxc5 bxc5
19. Bd3 f4 20. Be2 Nd7 21. Bg4 Nf6 22. Bxc8 Qxc8 23. Nc3 g5 24. Rb6 $5 h5 25.
Nf3 $6 {Portisch' play has no power.} Qd8 26. Rc6 Rc8 $6 (26... g4 $1 27. hxg4
hxg4 28. Nh2 Qd7 {attacks on the kingside.}) 27. Nb5 Qd7 28. h4 gxh4 29. Rxc8
Rxc8 30. Nxh4 Nh6 31. Bd2 Re8 32. a4 Nfg4 33. f3 $2 {He could capture on a5.}
Qd8 $1 34. Nf5 Nxf5 35. exf5 Nh6 36. Kf2 $6 {He should protect f5.} Qh4+ $5 {
Pawn f5 could be captured.} 37. Ke2 $6 (37. Kg1 $1 Nxf5 38. Qc2 Rf8 39. Bc3 {
tries to survive in a difficult position.}) 37... Nxf5 $6 38. Nc3 $6 Rb8 39.
Ne4 Rb3 $1 40. Bc3 Ra3 41. Kd3 Ng3 42. Qc1 Nxe4 43. Rxe4 Ra2 44. Re2 Rxe2 45.
Kxe2 Qg3 46. Qf1 Qg6 47. Bd2 Qc2 48. Ke1 Bf6 49. g4 fxg3 50. Qh3 Qb3 51. Kf1
Qd3+ 52. Ke1 Qxf3 53. Qe6+ Kg7 {Najdorf benefited from Portisch' weak defence.}
0-1

